Limbo's Project:I started Limbo's Project originally for small business purpose, which I dreamed to be my extra support for school and living cost or either. But after I speak with a couple people about my idea, I thought I can bring more than just a deck of Tarot——delivering a style and a spirit, a brand. As a digital artist and designer, I know how exciting those little "sparks" that come out accidentally from a totally different artwork is. To be honest, Limbo's Deck came from a happy accident which bonded me together with it for the next 10 months. Design Progress:Always try something new:Apart from working on designs, I started learning materials and modern techs that can help me spread my idea wider and further. I have to say that was a really long and slow progress. Reading references, purchasing materials and running tests...Here's the final test I did on different card boards:300gm Silver Card Board, Laser Print, 100% Dot300gm Copper Card board, Laser Print, 100% Dot:300gm Copper Card board, Ink-Jet, 100% Dot:300gm Copper Card board, Ink-Jet/Laser Print Compare, 100% Dot:300gm Kraft Paper, Laser Print, 70% Dot (Final):"Why not?"My artworks were deeply inspired by one of the greatest surrealism artist Salvador Dali, spend a couple minutes google him and you will see why. Lobster shaped telephone, lip shaped sofa, heart( not ❤) shaped jewelries... There are surprises every where as long as you started walking into his world, and "why not?" is the best, simplest answer for all your questions.There are three "why not" in Limbo's Deck.

Art style: Surreal dark fantasy, creepy fairy tale, industrial-gothic character designs;

Characterize each of the Majors: Instead of displaying a scene, I had each of the card possess into a careful designed ball jointed doll, and let them tell their own story;

A Logo of a fly? Just like the lobster shaped telephone in Dali's room.
Full Display of Limbo's Deck:Majors:There will be 3 different sizes for the copies of this deck:Compact: 9 x 5 cmRegular: 15 x 8.5 cmJumbo: 22 x 12.5 cmOther Materials/Media That Can Be Applied On:One of the most interesting thing I did was testing my prints on different materials.1.  Sketch Book:The book will be in A4 size ( larger than US letter) with printed hard kraft cover, don't forget to let me know your choice. Time to make some crazy art! 2. Water Tattoo:Cut them down, put them anywhere on your skin or other waterproof surface, apply some water and wait for 30s, then peel down slowly. Notice that it will take 3-4 days for the tattoo to start fading away, if you really want them to stay, get a real one XD. 3. PVC Card(Clear and non-clear version):When I was learning on hard materials, the plastic came to me first. Plastic are flexiable, anti-corrosion, easy to work with, color friendly(displaying)...Perfect material for both collecting and playing. Unfortunately the clear version might be too transparent to print both side, but it makes pertty nice unique collection!The card will be the same size like your bank card, and will be contained in a wood box with a wax seal on it. 4. Can Shaped Mug:I found this mug several months ago, the design is pretty cool, the 350ml is just the same size as the regular cans, and this one is refillable, and keep the temperature for several hours. 5. T-shirt Printing:The experience from my last project just inspired me a second time. Modal is a great fabric, when mixed with cotton, it makes way stretcher, higher absorbing, and better dyeing material. The print will be heat-transfered to the t-shirt in B&W. 6. The Aluminum/Alloy Deck( still testing):Aluminum alloy is one of the best amoung the matels. It has nice hardness, anti-impact, shining surface...Because of the funding problem, I can only test them by heat printing the image on the matel surface, which really cost me a lot of time and money, and the result was not very satisfying. The final pieces will be way better.The card will be the same size as Compact version, and will be contained in a wood box with a wax seal on it.What We Are Trying To Achieve In The Future:1. Color( WIP):It's very challengeing to make all 78 fully designed card into colored version, but we are making progress, and I'm very willing to share with you in the updates later. 2. Liquid transfer( Concept, Testing):Or low-temp transfering. Paint a special liquid on prints and stick it to wood( or other surfaces) to achieve full image transfering.3. 3D product and app.( WIP):Creating 3D model assets for each card, the finished pieces can be easily 3D printed in to sculptures, and farther be scripted into mobil apps.Dream starts small, ends up great"Intelligence without ambition is a bird without wings."——DaliHere's a glance of a corner of my bedroom which had already pilled with empty materials and a transfering machine. I started the project for not only support myself for my collect life, but also as an artist, I dare to show my ambition to the world.Thanks for your support!
